{
  "stem": "26111.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And it may seem strange, but even at the age of-- let's see, I would be eight when I started, eight or nine when I started going to the high school there, the gymnasium.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And at-- even before that time, I was very, very aware of what it was like to be a Jew.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The reason being, of course, the usual kind of discrimination at school, I say usual-- usual for Germany.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Not-- but it was quite usual there, as I soon was told.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "There wasn't any physical abuse, a lot verbal abuse, more or less forceful, more or less insulting, but always there.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I, I should add that religion in Europe was at that time-- and still is to a greater extent than in Anglo-Saxon countries-- a-- much more of a part of one's identity.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "On every identity document that I know of, whether it was a-- an identity card for use within the country, on a passport, whatever it might be, on the first page, among the vital statistics would be religion.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And that would be marked.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "In the same way, this was part of the identity that accompanies you everywhere-- accompanied you everywhere-- school, work, et cetera.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "You would-- it was not, not possible even to, to, to circumvent that or to, to escape it.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And if one belonged to a despised or disliked-- at least at first, disliked, later, despised and worst-- minority, i.e. the Jews, it was, of course, the, the, the, the, words, the foul language, the words that fell on the ears of children already from a very early age.",
      "word_count": 49
    }
  ],
